The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | FPAI plans awards function
                                                                                                                                     FPAI plans awards function
            A STAFF REPORTER            Bhaichung Bhutia                           
	Calcutta: The Football Players Association of India (FPAI), in association with McDowells No. 1 Celebration, plans to organise an awards function on December 13. The venue is yet to be decided.         
	Speaking at a press conference on Saturday, president Bhaichung Bhutia said: We have chosen four categories  best young player, best foreign player, best Indian player and best coach  where the performance of the previous season was considered.         
	The nominations were chosen by some of the senior players and the winners will be chosen by the 40 players who will be in Goa for the senior and under-23 probables camps.                                                                                                                       
